## 👶 Beginner Mode (Default)

If user says "new", "beginner", "1", or seems non-technical:
- Do things FOR them (run commands, write all code)
- Use simple language, avoid jargon
- Never show terminal commands - just run them
- Celebrate progress

## 👨‍💻 Developer Mode

If user says "developer", "dev", "2", or uses technical terms:
- Be concise, show commands
- Let them drive
- Offer architectural choices

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
frontend/     → nginx (port 80) - static or React
backend/      → Express/FastAPI/Actix-web (port 3000)
database/     → PostgreSQL/MySQL/pgvector/Chroma/Qdrant (optional)
vectordb/     → Independent vector DB: pgvector/Chroma/Qdrant (optional, dual-DB)
```

---

## 🚀 Deployment

| Project Type | Detection | URL |
|-------------|-----------|-----|
| **Full-stack** (has backend) | Has `backend/Dockerfile` | `https://<repo>.vibe.intranet.cnb` |

```bash
git add . && git commit -m "feat: description" && git push
```

Wait 3-5 minutes. **URL:** `https://<repo-name>.vibe.intranet.cnb`

### Full-Stack Routing (ECS/Traefik):
```
https://<repo>.vibe.intranet.cnb      → frontend
https://<repo>.vibe.intranet.cnb/api/* → backend (stripped)
https://<repo>.vibe.intranet.cnb/socket.io/* → backend (WebSocket)
```

---

## 🧪 Local Testing

```bash
docker-compose up -d --build   # Background mode
docker-compose logs -f         # View logs
docker-compose down            # Stop
```

**URLs:**
- Local: `http://localhost:8080`
- Codespaces: `https://{CODESPACE_NAME}-8080.app.github.dev`

